PN,30301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FScientists have discovered a way to
OL,7,F"hear" cosmic events like the
OL,8,Fcollision of black holes using a
OL,9,Fprocess similar to the pitch-
OL,10,Fcorrection used in music production.
OL,12,FExperts from the international Ligo,
OL,13,FVirgo and Kagra (LVK) gravitational
OL,14,Fwave observatory collaboration used
OL,15,Fthe technique to use gravitational-
OL,16,Fwave signals to measure the response
OL,17,Fof their incredibly sensitive
OL,18,Finstruments.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FThe technique, which they call
OL,7,Fastrophysical calibration, enables
OL,8,Fthem to ensure that they can clearly
OL,9,F"hear" the sounds of huge cosmic
OL,10,Fevents even when one gravitational
OL,11,Fwave detector is slightly out of tune.
OL,13,FThe researchers can account for subtle
OL,14,Fdistortions in the data by combining
OL,15,Fsignals from other detectors with
OL,16,Fprecise predictions from the laws of
OL,17,Fgravity.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FExperts said the process is similar to
OL,7,Fhow music production software such as
OL,8,FAuto-Tune can correct a singer's pitch
OL,9,Fif it is off key to meet the right
OL,10,Fnote.
OL,12,FThe findings are described in a paper
OL,13,Fpublished as a preprint on arXiv ahead
OL,14,Fof publication in the journal Physical
OL,15,FReview Letters.
OL,17,FDr Christopher Berry, of the
OL,18,FUniversity of Glasgow's Institute for
OL,19,FGravitational Research, is part of the
OL,20,FLVK collaboration and an author of the
OL,21,Fpaper.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FHe said: "Gravitational waves are
OL,7,Fripples in spacetime that stretch and
OL,8,Fsqueeze space. They are tiny by the
OL,9,Ftime that they reach the Earth,
OL,10,Fmillions of years after the events
OL,11,Fthat first created them.
OL,13,F"They are not something which we can
OL,14,Fhear, but our detectors can output the
OL,15,Fsignals as waveforms that we can
OL,16,Fincrease in pitch to listen to, with
OL,17,Feach signal producing their own
OL,18,Fdistinctive chirp.
OL,26,@nD@JOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,F"Those chirps encode a wealth of
OL,7,Finformation we can analyse to learn
OL,8,Fabout their sources: their masses,
OL,9,Fspins, distance, and location."
OL,11,FScientists said the gravitational-wave
OL,12,Fsignals used by the team to develop
OL,13,Ftheir astrophysical calibration
OL,14,Ftechnique are among the loudest ever
OL,15,Fdetected by the collaboration.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FThe first signal, picked up on
OL,7,FSeptember 25 2024 and named GW240925,
OL,8,Fwas produced by the merger of two
OL,9,Fblack holes between nine and seven
OL,10,Ftimes the mass of our sun more than a
OL,11,Fbillion light-years away.
OL,13,FThe second signal, on February 7 2025
OL,14,Fand named GW250207, was the second-
OL,15,Floudest signal in the nearly 200
OL,16,Fdetected by the collaboration in the
OL,17,Fdecade since the first detection in
OL,18,F2015.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FIt was produced by the collision of
OL,7,Ftwo black holes between 35 and 30
OL,8,Ftimes the mass of our sun about 600
OL,9,Fmillion light-years from Earth.
OL,11,FIn the paper LVK researchers
OL,12,Fdemonstrate how they turned the
OL,13,Fchallenge of analysing data collected
OL,14,Ffrom two gravitational wave signals
OL,15,Fdetected when Ligo Hanford was up and
OL,16,Frunning, but performing below its
OL,17,Fusual standard, into an opportunity to
OL,18,Fimprove the collaboration's ability to
OL,19,Fanalyse data.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FIt is hoped results could help future
OL,7,Fobserving runs of the international
OL,8,Fnetwork of LVK detectors in the USA,
OL,9,FJapan and Italy ensure that they
OL,10,Fproduce the most reliable results,
OL,11,Feven when the circumstances of the
OL,12,Fdetection are less than ideal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FDr Daniel Williams from the University
OL,7,Fof Glasgow's Institute for
OL,8,FGravitational Research, said: "These
OL,9,Fdiscoveries demonstrate that, over our
OL,10,Fdecade of work since the first
OL,11,Fdetection, we have developed a
OL,12,Fcomprehensive understanding of our
OL,13,Fentire analysis pipeline, from the
OL,14,Fsignals themselves to the detector
OL,15,Fbehaviour.
OL,26,@pD@_OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,F"In the rare instance that something
OL,7,Fgoes wrong with one detector, we now
OL,8,Fhave robust back-up methods to
OL,9,Fcompensate and leverage data from the
OL,10,Fother detectors to give us the best-
OL,11,Fquality results."
OL,13,FProfessor Stephen Fairhurst, of
OL,14,FCardiff University, who is the Ligo
OL,15,FScientific Collaboration's
OL,16,Fspokesperson, said: "It's remarkable
OL,17,Fthat these massive cosmic events can
OL,18,Fnot only be measured by our
OL,19,Finstruments, but actually used to
OL,20,Fcheck our measurements."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@QO]xD@UOU|D@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778652345
OL,3,CNew technique enables scientists to
OL,4,C'hear' black hole collisions
OL,6,FHe added: "We're moving from the era
OL,7,Fof first discoveries to the era of
OL,8,Fprecision gravitational wave
OL,9,Fastronomy. We can be confident that
OL,10,Four next observing runs will continue
OL,11,Fto build our rapidly-growing catalogue
OL,12,Fof gravitational-wave discoveries, and
OL,13,Fexpand our understanding of the
OL,14,Funiverse."
OL,16,FThe LVK Collaboration is a network of
OL,17,Fscientists who co-ordinate and
OL,18,Fcollaborate on the operation of the
OL,19,Fdetectors and on the production of the
OL,20,Fscientific results.
OL,26,@nD@KOUvD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
